description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler. Create a class in a subpackage such as:

package subpackage;

public class Test {

public static void main(String[] args) {

System.out.println("Hello");

}}

Then compile using the following command:

ajc -d subpackage\ subpackage\Test.java

You will see a directory "subpackage" created under the existing "subpackage" directory.

So, the expected behavior is to have the same behavior as javac.
